  "prompt": "How long does it take to transfer money through SBI ATM, from one SBI account to another SBI account?",
  "response": "Transferring money between two SBI accounts using an SBI ATM is typically processed instantly. Once the transfer is initiated, the funds should be transferred to the other account within a few minutes. However, the actual time may depend on the operational status of the ATM, network connectivity, and other factors. If any issues arise, it might take longer, and you may want to check for any notifications or alerts from SBI.\n\nFor the most accurate and up-to-date information, it's always best to check directly with SBI or refer to their official website.",
